<TITLE> President, PM issue Ramadan messages </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 22 (bdnews24.com)President Zillur Rahman and prime minister Sheikh Hasina gave separate Ramadan greetings on the eve of Ramadan on Saturday. "The holy month of Ramadan is a time for self-purification and infinite charity. This month paves the way for all humanity to seek the boundless charity and mercy of Allah," Zillur said ahead of the month of fasting, set to start Sunday. "Feelings of intimacy and a sense of fraternity becomes stronger among people, irrespective of whether they are rich or poor, in the month of Ramadan," he said. In her Ramadan message to the people, Hasina said everyone must work together to create a lasting peace and avoid all wrongdoing. "We can maintain the purity of Ramadan through the practice of thrift, patience and restraint," said Hasina. 
